abstract: It's an ill wind that blows through the newest addition to Mr. Keats's "Peter" books (others, "Whistle for Willie," "The Snowy Day," "Peter's Chair"). A gust from a gathering storm sends Peter's very special handwritten invitation to his birthday party sailing down the street with yellow-slickered Peter in pursuit.
